# VodHub Frontend — Project Overview

VodHub frontend is the frontend of the VodHub pnpm monorepo, a video aggregation player built with Vite + React.

## Core Features
- Vite + React Router (client-side rendering)
- Aggregates multiple video sources, supports category browsing, search, playback
- Multi-theme support (midnight, aurora, cyber)
- Built-in CMS management interface

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Vite + React 19 + React Router + TypeScript
- **State Management**: Zustand
- **UI Library**: Ant Design 6
- **Styling**: SCSS Modules + CSS variables (multi-theme)
- **HTTP Client**: Axios
- **Video Player**: xgplayer + HLS.js
- **Package Manager**: pnpm (monorepo at root)

## Video Sources Management

- **Store**: `lib/store/useVideoSourcesStore.ts` (Zustand + localStorage)
- **Built-in Sources**: Defined in `src/data/builtin-cms.json`
- **CMS Management UI**: `components/cms-management/index.tsx`
- Features: Enable/disable built-in sources, full CRUD for custom sources

## Development Tools
- **Linting**: ESLint + Prettier
- **Git Hooks**: Husky + lint-staged
- **Commits**: Commitlint + commitizen (conventional commits)

## Environment Requirements
- Node.js >= 24
- pnpm >= 10

## Development Commands

```bash
pnpm dev                          # Start both backend + frontend dev servers
pnpm dev:frontend                 # Frontend only (vite dev)
pnpm --filter @vodhub/frontend build     # Production build (standalone)
pnpm --filter @vodhub/frontend lint      # ESLint check
pnpm --filter @vodhub/frontend typecheck # TypeScript type check
pnpm format                       # Prettier write all apps
pnpm format:check                 # Prettier check
pnpm commit                       # Interactive conventional commit
```
